RELEASE NOTE
Refund Service – Version 1.2.0
INTRODUCTION:
This release introduces improvements in refund processing. It focuses on handling refund failures, improving UPI refund queries, and adding better tracking for SFTP failures.
OVERVIEW:
This release enhances refund reliability by fixing failure scenarios and improving query performance. It also introduces a new status to track cases where SFTP processing fails.
CODE CHANGES / CONFIG / DB CHANGES:
Implemented refund failure handling improvements
Fixed issues in refund failed scenarios
Modified booked refund UPI query for better performance
Added new status "refundProcess" when SFTP fails
PREVIOUS IMPACT:
Refund failures were not handled properly
Issues in refund failed scenarios
UPI refund query performance issues
No proper status when SFTP failed
IMPACT OF CHANGES:
Improved refund failure handling
Better stability in refund processing
Optimized UPI refund query performance
Ability to track SFTP failures using new status
ROLLBACK PLAN:
Revert refund service code changes
Restore previous refund processing behavior
RELEASE NOTE
Operation Service – Version 1.4.0
INTRODUCTION:
This release introduces enhancements in reconciliation, file handling, and system stability. It also includes a Spring Boot upgrade and security fixes.
OVERVIEW:
This release focuses on improving reconciliation accuracy for multi-account transactions, enhancing file processing through SFTP, and fixing production issues. It also improves monitoring and system reliability.
CODE CHANGES / CONFIG / DB CHANGES:
Improved reconciliation process for multi-account transactions
Updated settlement status to COMPLETED
Fixed data synchronization issues
Upgraded Spring Boot from 3.3.10 to 3.5.9 and fixed vulnerabilities
Handled "null" string values in multi-account parsing
Added file path validation
Uploaded recon bad records file to RECON/OUT folder
Added SFTP OUT path configuration
Implemented checksum validation
Added DB synonyms and grants for APPADMIN
Enabled actuator health, liveness, and readiness checks
Ignored negative amount while parsing recon file
Fixed incorrect bank reference number issue in production
PREVIOUS IMPACT:
Reconciliation issues in multi-account transactions
Incorrect settlement status updates
Data synchronization inconsistencies
File handling and validation issues
Negative amounts causing parsing problems
Incorrect bank reference number in production
Limited monitoring capability
IMPACT OF CHANGES:
Improved reconciliation accuracy
Correct settlement status handling
Stable data synchronization
Better file validation and SFTP handling
Improved system monitoring using actuator
Increased security with dependency upgrades
Correct handling of bank reference numbers
Cleaner recon processing
ROLLBACK PLAN:
Revert operation service code changes
Restore previous reconciliation and file handling behavior
Rollback Spring Boot version if required
